{"word":"περιδινέω","slug":"περιδινέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>περιδινέω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>ήσω</el>) </el><p/><i>to whirl</i> or <i>wheel round</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschines'>Aeschin.</a></b>: —<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to run circling round</i>, <el>πόλιν περιδινηθήτην</el> (3 dual aor1 <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a>) <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>:—so in <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b>; <i>to spin round</i> like a top, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/>"}]}